Define Documentation

#define PLCRASH_REPORT_FILE_VERSION   1

Crash format version byte identifier.

Will not change outside of the introduction of an entirely new crash log format.

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum PLCrashReportArchitecture

Indicates the architecture under which a Crash Log was generated.

Deprecated:
The architecture value has been deprecated in v1.1 and later crash reports. All new reports will make use of the new PLCrashReportProcessorInfo CPU type encodings.
Enumerator:

enum PLCrashReportProcessorTypeEncoding

The type encodings supported for CPU types and subtypes.

Currently only Apple Mach-O defined encodings are supported.
